            "id": "https://adrienleger.com/about.html",
            "url": "https://adrienleger.com/about.html",
            "title": "About me",
            "summary": "I am&hellip;",
            "content_html": "<h2 class=\"md-end-block md-heading md-focus\" ><figure class=\"post__image post__image--wide\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/banner_adrien_work.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" srcset=\"https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/banner_adrien_work-xs.jpg 300w ,https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/banner_adrien_work-sm.jpg 480w ,https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/banner_adrien_work-md.jpg 749w ,https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/banner_adrien_work-xl.jpg 1200w\"  alt=\"\" width=\"1155\" height=\"297\"></figure></h2>\n<p>I am a <strong>computational biologist</strong> currently working as a senior postdoc at the EMBL-EBI in Ewan Birney's Team. I have a <strong>dual background in molecular biology and bioinformatics. </strong>My PhD was at the bench in <strong>virology</strong> and <strong>epigenetics</strong> at the INSERM 1089 (University of Nantes, France). After my PhD, I was promoted to a junior team leader position and obtained an additional master's degree in bioinformatics, while developing expertise in sequencing methods related to viral vector genomes. I then moved to the EMBL-EBI to expand my skills in data analysis and software development. At the EBI, I have been working on a broad range of topics including <strong>RNA modifications in cancer</strong> and more recently medaka fish <strong>functional genomics</strong>, developing a deep knowledge of <strong>nanopore sequencing.</strong></p>\n<p>During my career, I have contributed to over 20 scientific publications and communications. Have a look at my <a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=SA5LcXgAAAAJ\">Google Scholar Profile<img loading=\"lazy\" style=\"padding: 5px;\" src=\"https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/scholar.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" srcset=\"https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/scholar-xs.png 300w ,https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/scholar-sm.png 480w ,https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/scholar-md.png 749w ,https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/scholar-xl.png 1200w\"  alt=\"\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\"></a> or my <a href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8772-6776\">ORCID Profile<img loading=\"lazy\" style=\"padding: 5px;\" src=\"https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/orcid.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" srcset=\"https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/orcid-xs.png 300w ,https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/orcid-sm.png 480w ,https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/orcid-md.png 749w ,https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/orcid-xl.png 1200w\"  alt=\"\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\"></a> to know more about my academic track record or learn about my preferred publications in the <a href=\"https://adrienleger.com/publications-and-communication.html\">top publications tab 📚</a>. As a computational biologist, I have been writing dozens of scripts, APIs and analytic workflows. At the EBI, I have developed or co-developed a number of tools to analyse Oxford Nanopore sequencing data, which have cumulatively been downloaded over 100,000 times. For more details see the <a href=\"https://adrienleger.com/software.html\">software development tab 💻</a> or my <a href=\"https://github.com/a-slide\">Github profile<img loading=\"lazy\" style=\"padding: 5px;\" src=\"https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/github.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" srcset=\"https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/github-xs.png 300w ,https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/github-sm.png 480w ,https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/github-md.png 749w ,https://adrienleger.com/media/posts/2/responsive/github-xl.png 1200w\"  alt=\"\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\"></a></p>\n<h2>My personal life</h2>\n<p class=\"\"><span class=\"md-line md-end-block\" >I am also the dad of a bright and hyperactive 2 year old boy, meaning that most of my personal life is spent being a clown, coach, cook, tower builder, cleaner... Which I enjoy, obviously.</span></p>\n<p class=\"\"><span class=\"md-line md-end-block\" >I am climbing/bouldering on a regular basis but nowhere as much as in secondary school, where I met my wonderful partner. Cycling is the other big drive of my life. As far as I can remember I have always been into cycling, one way or another. </span><span class=\"md-line md-end-block\" ><span class=\"\">Crazy as it might seem, our little family is planning a 1 year long cycling journey across Europe and Asia... Yes it is for real.</span></span></p>",
